A Georgia road about 125 miles away from where Duane Allman died nearly 45 years ago took the life of one of the Southern rockers who played on the hit dedicated to the Allman Brothers guitarist .
The former drummer and a founding member of Lynyrd Skynyrd , Robert ` Bob ' Burns Jr , died late in a single-vehicle crash near Cartersville , Georgia .
Burns ' vehicle went off the road just before midnight as it approached a curve .
Burns , 64 , was killed in the wreck .